{"lemma":"حِلْفَيْ","slug":"حِلْفَيْ","root":"ح.ل.ف","root_slug":"ح-ل-ف","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ل-ف","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"حِلْف","root":"حلف","pos":"V","occurrence_count":12},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n8843","","n8847","n8848"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%90%D9%84%D9%92%D9%81%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to swear"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make swear, to put to oath, to swear in"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to adjure, to entreat earnestly"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"oath"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"alliance; federation, pact","examples":[{"text":"حِلْف وَارْسَو","english":"Warsaw Pact"},{"text":"حِلْفُ شِمَالِ الْأَطْلَنْطِيِّ","english":"North Atlantic Alliance (NATO)"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ally"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ħa.la.fa/","/ħal.la.fa/","/ħalf/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n8843","headword_ar":"حَلَفَ","root":"Hlf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HalifN","text_ar":"حَلِفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HalofN","text_ar":"حَلْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HilofN","text_ar":"حِلْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHoluwfN","text_ar":"مَحْلُوفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"majoluwdN","text_ar":"مَجْلُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoquwlN","text_ar":"مَعْقُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEosuwrN","text_ar":"مَعْسُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHoluwfapN","text_ar":"مَحْلُوفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, K) [and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHoluwfaA='u","text_ar":"مَحْلُوفَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$oEuwraA='u","text_ar":"مَشْعُورَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as will be seen from what follows],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He swore."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Halaba biA@ll~`hi","text_ar":"حَلَبَ بِا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He swore by God"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Halafa A_in~hu ka*aA","text_ar":"حَلَفَ اـِنّهُ كَذَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He swore it was so."},{"kind":"text","text":"And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Halafa lahu EalaY ka*aA","text_ar":"حَلَفَ لَهُ عَلَى كَذَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He swore to him to do such a thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Halafa yamiynFA","text_ar":"حَلَفَ يَمِينًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vnY","text_ar":"ثنى"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c.) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY yamiynK","text_ar":"عَلَى يَمِينٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(El-Jámi' es Sagheer voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano","text_ar":"مَنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c.) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He swore an oath"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA wamaHoluwfaAy^ihi laA A^afoEalu","text_ar":"لَا وَمَحْلُوفَايِهِ لَا اَفْعَلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"No, by the swearing it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"no, I swear it,"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will not do"},{"kind":"text","text":"such a thing]. (Ibn-Buzurj, K. *) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHoluwfapF biA@ll~`hi","text_ar":"مَحْلُوفَةً بِا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHolifu maHoluwfapF","text_ar":"اَحْلِفُ مَحْلُوفَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I swear"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an oath"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by God"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Lth, K.) Accord. to IAth, the primary signification of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HalifN","text_ar":"حَلِفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is The act of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"confederating,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"making a compact"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"confederacy, to aid,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"assist;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"making an agreement:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[but this meaning is afterwards said in the TA to be tropical:] when the object of this, in the time of paganism, was to aid in sedition or the like, and in fighting, and incursions into the territories of enemies, it was forbidden by Mohammad: when the object was to aid the wronged, and for making close the ties of relationship, and the like, he confirmed it. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","Lth"]},{"entry_id":"n8847","headword_ar":"حِلْفٌ","root":"Hlf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A confederacy, league, compact,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"covenant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between persons;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HilofapN","text_ar":"حِلْفَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) because it is not concluded, or ratified, but by swearing. (ISd, TA.) ―         -b2-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Friendship;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"true,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sincere, friendship."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)       -A2-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A confederate"},{"kind":"text","text":"of another;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one who unites in a confederacy, league, compact,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"covenant;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaliyfN","text_ar":"حَلِيفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Msb, K, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a friend,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sincere friend, who swears to his companion that he will not act unfaithfully with him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or a friend, or true friend, is thus called because he so swears; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaliyfN","text_ar":"حَلِيفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) pl. of the former"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHolaAfN","text_ar":"اَحْلَافٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, * K;) and of the latter"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HulafaA='u","text_ar":"حُلَفَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) By the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHlAf","text_ar":"احلاف"},{"kind":"text","text":"are meant, in a poem of Zuheyr, Asad and Ghatafán; because they united in a confederacy to aid each other; and the same appellation is applied to a party of Thakeef; (S, K;) and to six tribes of Kureysh, namely, 'Abd-ed-Dár, Kaab, Jumah, Sahm, Makhzoom, and 'Adee: (K:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaliyfaAni","text_ar":"الحَلِيفَانِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"to Benoo-Asad and Teiyi, (S, O, K,) or Asad and Ghatafán; (ISd, TA;) and Fezárah and Asad also (S, K) are termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaliyfaAni","text_ar":"حَلِيفَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA","O"]},{"entry_id":"n8848","headword_ar":"حَلَفٌ","root":"Hlf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HalofaA='","text_ar":"حَلْفَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}